<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">560.M3/23: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase—Extract]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-21T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 21,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>63. …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>Department has received since June 15 insistent requests from film
                            interests which urge a very strong stand. A subsequent telegram may take
                            up this subject.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>